p.paragraph.
  If an action only requires one step (e.g. sending a feedback) then it can be packed into a popover.

.example
  .example__header
    .example__device-selection
      .example__device-selection__device.example__device-selection__device--mobile
      .example__device-selection__device.example__device-selection__device--tablet
      .example__device-selection__device.example__device-selection__device--desktop.is-active
  .example__content.example__content--centered
      iframe.example__iframe
      .example__html(data-example-centered)
        div(style="min-height: 400px")
          a.button(id='toggleButton',data-popover='#popover') Show Popover
          .popover(id='popover')
            .popover__tail
            .popover__box
              .popover__box__header
                a.popover__close
                  svg.modal__close-icon.icon-svg
                    use(xmlns:xlink='http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink',xlink:href=relative('/images/icons.svg#modal-close'))
                .popover__box__header__headline Demo
              .popover__box__content__wrapper
                .popover__box__content
                  textarea.control.control--textarea
                  p.paragraph
                    a.button.button--small 'clicky click'


h3.heading.heading--tertiary UX Checklist
ul.checklist
  li.checklist__item Use sparingly and only for selected actions.
  li.checklist__item Mobile: Slide it up and present it in full screen.
